piano

Class Piano

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Thread
      • tech_demo.TechDemo
        • piano.Piano
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable, java.util.Observer

    public class Piano
extends TechDemo
implements java.util.Observer
    This class will implement a way to play piano directly from the launchpad, with proper keys displayed on it and instant audio (either will be samples or will send MIDI to an external MIDI compatible piano synthesizer - Pianoteq 2.2 - for even more close to real piano sound).
    Version:
    $Revision: 1.0 $
    Author:
    Helion

      • shiftVelocity

        private void shiftVelocity(boolean upOrDown)
        Shifts the simulated velocity of key presses. This is because the Launchpad S is not velocity sensitive, therefore the only way to change the volume of the key presses is to shift the velocity
        Parameters:
        upOrDown - True if increasing velocity, False otherwise

      • sustainButtonPressed

        private void sustainButtonPressed(boolean pressed,
                                  boolean cutSustain)
        Emulates a Piano's sustain pedal: keeps all notes active until either the sustain is released, or until a temporary Sustain cut is pressed
        Parameters:
        pressed - True if the sustain is initiated, false if it is to be stopped
        cutSustain - False if the Sustain button was pressed, True if the temporary Cut Sustain button was pressed
